com.splunk.journal.hadoop

Class RecordReaderHelper

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.splunk.journal.hadoop.RecordReaderHelper

  • public class RecordReaderHelper
extends java.lang.Object
    Helper class for hadoop RecordReader classes that reads Splunk/Hunk raw-data journal files. Placing configuration and formatting information in a helper class ensures consistency between the "old-style" and "new-style" implementations.

    One key-value pair will be read for each event. Both the key and the value are TSV-formatted sets of fields. By default, the value will be the tuple:

        _time _indextime sourcetype host source _raw

    All of these fields have the same meaning as they would in Splunk SPL (ie. search processing language). The default value of the key will be eventOffsetInFile, which indicates the byte-offset in the uncompressed raw-data file at which the event was read.

    The key and value formats can be overridden by setting Configuration properties for, respectively, com.splunk.journal.hadoop.key_format and com.splunk.journal.hadoop.value_format. These can be given as values any comma-separated list of field names. If a field is not available for a given event, the cell in the TSV text will be represented by the empty string. Any indexed field may be used, but fields that would be extracted by Splunk at search-time will not be available.

    The separator character (by default a tab) can be changed by setting the Configuration property for com.splunk.journal.hadoop.separator_char.

    The escape character (by default a backslash (e.g. '\') can be changed by setting the Configuration property for com.splunk.journal.hadoop.escape_char.

    By default, if the code encounters badly formatted data, it throws an Exception. This can be changed via the Configuration property com.splunk.journal.hadoop.suppress.exceptions. If set to true, the code will log such exceptions and act as though the data stream has finished.
